                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00111 A.R./1325: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-24T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 24, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>131. Your 263, June 23, 7 p.m. Please inform Guani that his feeling regarding
                    special representations by our Minister in Paraguay has been conveyed to Mr.
                    Frost with the Department’s strong support.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
